<exercise checkit-seed="0008" checkit-slug="CC3" checkit-title="Constant-Coefficient Linear Homogeneous Higher-Order ODEs">
  <statement>
    <p>Explain how to find the general solution to each given ODE using
        exponential functions.</p>
    <p>For each exponential solution using complex numbers, also provide
        an alternate general solution using only real numbers.</p>
      <ol>
        <li>
            <me>-20 \, {y'} = 2 \, {y''} + 50 \, {y}</me>
        </li>
        <li>
            <me>6 \, {y'} + 3 \, {y'''} = -9 \, {y''}</me>
        </li>
        <li>
            <me>-3 \, {y''} - 24 \, {y'} = 96 \, {y}</me>
        </li>
      </ol>
  </statement>
  <answer>
      <ol>
        <li><me>
            
            {y} = k_{1} t e^{\left(-5 \, t\right)} + k_{2} e^{\left(-5 \, t\right)}
         </me></li>
        <li><me>
            
            {y} = k_{2} e^{\left(-t\right)} + k_{1} e^{\left(-2 \, t\right)} + k_{3}
         </me></li>
        <li><me>
            {y} = c_{1} e^{\left(4 \, i t - 4 \, t\right)} + c_{2} e^{\left(-4 \, i t - 4 \, t\right)};\qquad
            {y} = {\left(k_{1} \cos\left(4 \, t\right) + k_{2} \sin\left(4 \, t\right)\right)} e^{\left(-4 \, t\right)}
         </me></li>
      </ol>
  </answer>
</exercise>
